caption: A couple makes their way down a quiet Gayley Avenue, away from Westwood’s bustling nightlife.
The typically busy underpass is barren, aside from a student making his way through the night.
Custodial workers scrub the UCLA Athletics Hall of Fame in the middle of the night.
Trash litters the benches along Bruin Walk.
Sandwiches accompany a late-night cram session in The Study at Hedrick.
Students staff the John Wooden Center from night until morning. The gym extended its opening hours beginning winter 2017.

"All my classes are heavy on reading (this quarter), so I have to sacrifice sleep sometimes,” said Arman Antonyan, a first-year political science student. “Despite being a night person, I always end up regretting not sleeping enough.”

"I've been here (at Powell) all night doing work for my off-campus job,” said Alexandra Polovneff, a fourth-year psychobiology student. “I conduct social psychology research for an investment firm, and I have a deadline to meet.”
Early morning gym sessions are a routine for fourth-year sociology student Angel Cantellano. “[I] come here Tuesdays through Thursdays. I prefer to come early when there’s less people.”
The Hilgard apartments, normally alive with construction workers remodeling the building, are quiet this morning.
Morning commuters await their bus rides in Westwood.
Reserve Officers’ Training Corps students start off their day with an intense morning.
Students trek to their early morning classes.

While the hills by Janss Steps are normally dotted with students relaxing or enjoying the view, this morning they are comparatively empty. A groundskeeper takes advantage of the quiet morning to mow the sprawling lawn.
Students squeeze in some last-minute questions following a lecture in the Math Sciences building.
Baristas at Evelyn & Mo Ostin Music Cafe in Schoenberg Music Building prepare a selection of coffees for the day.
Siem Ingelse, a graduate exchange student from Amsterdam studying screenwriting, and his friend, David van Boven enjoy some sun by the Los Angeles Tennis Center.
Second-year biology student Alex Phu facilitates a Southeast Asian Campus Learning Education and Retention peer-counseling session with third-year chemical engineering student Fatin Bakri.
A groundskeeper trims bushes outside Haines Hall.
Third-year linguistics and computer science student Thomas Palmer strums a dulcimer, a fretted string instrument considered to be the ancestor of the piano, by the Sunken Gardens.
Students lounge in between class outside Broad Art Center.
Though John Wooden Center is open for 24 hours, many prefer to hit the gym for a midday sweat session.
Pediatric AIDS Coalition members recruit prospective dancers for the annual Dance Marathon.
Hammer Museum crewmembers Paris Patt (left) and Elizabeth Patt (right) perform routine maintenance on statues in the Murphy Sculpture Garden.
Some students scramble to class, while others pass out flyers for their clubs. Others stop by to check out the numerous organizations holding fundraisers.
Third-year gender studies student Natalie Ebrahams reviews her notes in Royce Hall’s iconic arches as she awaits her next class.
Students bask in the California winter sun on the rolling hills by Janss Steps.

Second-year Arabic and French languages and cultures student Bilqis Kulungu (left) and second-year physiological science student Asha Isse (right) sign petitions against University of California tuition hikes.
Lucy, a goldendoodle, comes for a walk with her owner on UCLA’s campus almost every day.
A campus tour concludes with a Q&A session with fourth-year business economics student Andi Wong in front of Wooden.
Event staffer Maurice Moore finishes his dinner outside Pauley Pavilion before a UCLA men's volleyball game against Penn State.
A student snaps a photo of the sunset while atop Janss Steps.
Kerckhoff Hall, home of many UCLA student organizations, illuminates Bruin Walk at night.
The UCLA Anderson School of Management hosts its third annual Consumer Electronics Show event, which focuses on artificial intelligence, digital reality and biometrics.
AMP'D Entertainment employees pack up the equipment at Anderson after CES.

UCLA design media arts alumnus Alec Maassen admires the artwork from the annual design | media arts undergraduate exhibition. This year, artists explored interpretations of the prefix ‘dis.’ from Jan. 18 to Feb. 2.
The fraternity houses are quiet on a Thursday night following the temporary ban on alcohol in fraternity house parties, which was implemented Jan. 18.
Students await the Campus Events Commission’s screening of “Loving Vincent” at Ackerman Grand Ballroom.
Third-year astrophysics student Matt Jacobs (left), along with his team, won their intramural soccer match 9-0.

Bruin Bhangra, consisting of 25 students passionate about Punjabi culture and dance, practices throughout the year. The club hosts an annual dance competition for other collegiate Bhangra teams each spring.
The club tennis team occupies most of the Los Angeles Tennis Center at night to practice.
Fourth-year biology student Stephanie Hernandez, along with other members NSU Modern, run through another portion of their latest dance routine.
